                        <summary>A single copper plate found in a group of five copper plates of the Parijātavaneśvara temple of Tirukkaḷar, found altogether strung on a copper ring. Records a donation of paddy to the Mahādeva of Tirukkaḷar for offerings at festival time. Time of Kulottuṅga I Cōḻa.</summary>
